gomodel:SYNGO_3957  a    owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment     "Rationale: Quantitative immuno-gold EM in macaque monkey enthorynal cortex show that EAAC1 is present predominantly at the edge of the PSD (peri-PSD) in the spine plasma membrane. These data are replicated in rodent hippocampus tissue (see supporting refs). No significant immuno-reactivity is observed in the presynaptic terminal. As EAAC1 is a transporter with several transmembrane regions (see UniProt F7H624 (F7H624_MACMU)), the localisation is integral to the spine membrane.. Experimental description: Macaque monkey (Macaca fascicularis): from text (no specific M&M here) \"Four adult male long-tailed macaque monkeys (Macaca fascicularis) were used in this study. \"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate  "production" ;
        dc:contributor   "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date          "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title         "SYNGO_CC_3957" ;
        pav:providedBy   "https://syngo.vu.nl" .

